<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<worksheet >
    <title>EL-3 Modeling with Exponential Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete one part with progress on the other to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
      <introduction><p>The spreading of a rumor through a high school of 1000 students is modeled by 
        the logistic function <m>N(t) = \frac{1000}{1 + 49e^{-0.6t}}</m>, where <m>N(t)</m> is the 
        number of students who have heard the rumor after <m>t</m> days.</p>
    <p><em>Set up and solve each
          of the following.  Leave your answers as integers, simplified fractions or in terms of natural logarithms.</em></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>How many students knew the rumor initially?</p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>How many days will it take for 500 students to have heard the rumor?</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    
  </page>
</worksheet>